-Go to law school. 

1182
01:12:35,400 --> 01:12:39,080
Mom and Dad'll be able to afford it.
-Harold. 

1183
01:12:39,120 --> 01:12:41,240
Mama expects great things
from you. 

1184
01:12:42,640 --> 01:12:45,080
Can I--
Can I get you anything?

1185
01:12:48,120 --> 01:12:49,960
Relax, Dick. 

1186
01:12:50,040 --> 01:12:53,120
It's just me, huh?

1187
01:12:58,800 --> 01:13:00,920
The desert's so beautiful,
isn't it?

1188
01:13:06,040 --> 01:13:10,040
I want to go home, Dick. 

1189
01:13:10,120 --> 01:13:11,960
Time to go home. 

1190
01:13:13,240 --> 01:13:15,320
You--

1191
01:13:15,400 --> 01:13:18,680
You're not gonna quit on me now,
are you, Harold?

1192
01:13:45,920 --> 01:13:50,360
Down came the rain
and washed the spider out

1193
01:14:01,440 --> 01:14:03,200
Richard. 

1194
01:14:06,480 --> 01:14:08,440
I can't. 

1195
01:14:08,520 --> 01:14:10,800
You must. 

1196
01:14:10,880 --> 01:14:15,160
This law school, it's a gift
from thy brother. 

1197
01:14:15,240 --> 01:14:18,480
He had to die
For me to get it?

1198
01:14:22,160 --> 01:14:24,480
Something has to come
Of this. 

1199
01:14:26,400 --> 01:14:29,200
It's meant
to make us stronger. 

1200
01:14:29,280 --> 01:14:32,840
Thee art stronger than Harold,
Stronger than Arthur. 

1201
01:14:32,920 --> 01:14:36,680
God has chosen thee
to survive. 

1202
01:14:36,720 --> 01:14:38,680
What about happiness,
Mother?

1203
01:14:40,200 --> 01:14:43,560
Thee will find thy peace
At the center, Richard. 

1204
01:14:44,680 --> 01:14:47,480
Strength in this life, 

1205
01:14:47,560 --> 01:14:50,200
happiness in the next. 

1206
01:15:32,320 --> 01:15:34,720
Hey! Hey!

1207
01:15:34,800 --> 01:15:37,040
Now tell me you didn't
Want this, Buddy. 

1208
01:15:46,200 --> 01:15:48,840
Hey!

1209
01:16:06,160 --> 01:16:09,320
When the strongest nation
in the world can be tied down

1210
01:16:09,400 --> 01:16:11,720
for four years
in a war in Vietnam

1211
01:16:11,760 --> 01:16:13,760
with no end in sight;

1212
01:16:13,840 --> 01:16:17,840
when the richest nation in the world
can't manage its own economy;

1213
01:16:17,920 --> 01:16:21,240
when the nation with the greatest
tradition of the rule of law

1214
01:16:21,320 --> 01:16:24,560
is plagued by
unprecedented lawlessness;

1215
01:16:24,640 --> 01:16:28,240
when a nation that has been known for
a century for equality of opportunity

1216
01:16:28,320 --> 01:16:31,880
is torn by unprecedented
racial violence

1217
01:16:31,920 --> 01:16:35,240
when the president of the United States
cannot travel abroad

1218
01:16:35,280 --> 01:16:37,200
or to any major city
at home

1219
01:16:37,280 --> 01:16:39,880
without fear
of a hostile demonstration, 

1220
01:16:39,960 --> 01:16:43,840
then it is time for new leadership
for the United States of America. 

1221
01:16:47,520 --> 01:16:51,440
As we look at America, we see cities
enveloped in smoke and flame, 

1222
01:16:51,520 --> 01:16:53,960
millions of Americans
crying out in anguish, 

1223
01:16:54,040 --> 01:16:56,160
''Did we come all the way
for this?

1224
01:16:56,240 --> 01:17:00,400
Did American boys die in Normandy
and Valley Forge for this?''

1225
01:17:02,160 --> 01:17:05,080
I pledge to you
That the current wave of violence

1226
01:17:05,160 --> 01:17:07,400
will not be the wave
of the future. 

1227
01:17:09,960 --> 01:17:12,560
Let us begin by committing ourselves

1228
01:17:12,640 --> 01:17:15,600
to the truth--to find the truth,
to speak the truth

1229
01:17:15,680 --> 01:17:17,520
and to live the truth. 

1230
01:17:17,600 --> 01:17:20,720
A new voice is being heard
across America today. 

1231
01:17:20,800 --> 01:17:23,680
It is not the voice
Of the protesters or the shouters. 

1232
01:17:23,760 --> 01:17:27,400
It is the quiet voice of the majority
Of Americans who've been forgotten--

1233
01:17:27,440 --> 01:17:31,520
the non-shouters,
the, uh, non-demonstrators. 

1234
01:17:31,600 --> 01:17:36,000
They're the good people. They work hard
and they save and they pay their taxes. 

1235
01:17:36,080 --> 01:17:38,560
Now, who are they?
Let me tell you who they are. 

1236
01:17:38,640 --> 01:17:41,280
They're in this audience
by the thousands. 

1237
01:17:41,320 --> 01:17:43,080
They're the white Americans
and black Americans, 

1238
01:17:43,160 --> 01:17:45,680
Mexican and Italian Americans. 

1239
01:17:45,760 --> 01:17:48,000
They're the great
silent majority, 

1240
01:17:48,040 --> 01:17:50,120
and they have
become angry, finally. 

1241
01:17:50,200 --> 01:17:52,160
Angry, not with hate,
But angry, my friends, 

1242
01:17:52,200 --> 01:17:54,080
because they love America

1243
01:17:54,120 --> 01:17:57,200
and they don't like what's happened
to America these last four years. 

1244
01:17:57,280 --> 01:17:59,400
Let us understand. 

1245
01:17:59,480 --> 01:18:03,240
North Vietnam cannot defeat
or humiliate the United States. 

1246
01:18:03,320 --> 01:18:05,280
Only Americans
can do that!

1247
01:18:08,520 --> 01:18:10,440
I say to you tonight--

1248
01:18:10,520 --> 01:18:14,720
I say to you tonight we must have
a new feeling of responsibility, 

1249
01:18:14,760 --> 01:18:16,280
of self-discipline. 

1250
01:18:16,360 --> 01:18:18,440
We must look to renew
state and local government. 

1251
01:18:18,520 --> 01:18:22,440
We must have a complete reform of a big,
bloated federal government. 

1252
01:18:22,480 --> 01:18:25,360
Those of us in public service know

1253
01:18:25,440 --> 01:18:27,840
we can have full prosperity
in peacetime. 

1254
01:18:27,920 --> 01:18:30,480
Yes, we can cut
the defence budget. 

1255
01:18:30,560 --> 01:18:33,360
We can reduce, uh,
conventional forces in Europe. 

1256
01:18:33,440 --> 01:18:35,480
We can restore
the natural environment. 

1257
01:18:35,560 --> 01:18:38,560
We can improve health care and make it
more available to all people. 

1258
01:18:38,640 --> 01:18:42,000
And yes, we can have
a complete reform of this government. 

1259
01:18:42,080 --> 01:18:45,320
We can have a new
American revolution!

1260
01:18:57,640 --> 01:19:01,160
The whole world is watching!

1261
01:19:01,440 --> 01:19:03,720
The whole world is watching!

1262
01:19:09,720 --> 01:19:11,760
It'd be a disaster. 

1263
01:19:11,840 --> 01:19:14,920
There's a lot of sympathy
out there for Cambodia. 

1264
01:19:15,000 --> 01:19:17,840
Tiny, little, neutral
Buddhist country. 

1265
01:19:17,920 --> 01:19:20,960
They'll be rioting in the streets,
on your front lawn!

1266
01:19:21,000 --> 01:19:22,880
Building the
Cambodian army up?

1267
01:19:22,920 --> 01:19:25,520
My God, that would be harder
than a Vietnamese Army. 

1268
01:19:25,600 --> 01:19:28,240
They have no tradition. 

1269
01:19:28,320 --> 01:19:30,960
Mr. President, the government
there will collapse. 

1270
01:19:31,040 --> 01:19:33,600
So you're saying, do nothing.
-No, sir, continue the bombing. 

1271
01:19:33,680 --> 01:19:36,080
The same old horseshit.
Well, that's not good enough. 

1272
01:19:36,160 --> 01:19:38,520
I'm sick of being pushed around
by the, uh, Vietnamese

1273
01:19:38,600 --> 01:19:42,800
like we're some, uh,
you know, pitiful giant. 

1274
01:19:42,880 --> 01:19:46,560
They're using our P. O. W. s
to humiliate us. 

1275
01:19:46,600 --> 01:19:48,640
What we need now
is a bold move into Cambodia, 

1276
01:19:48,720 --> 01:19:51,600
and go right after their,
uh, V. C. base camps, 

1277
01:19:51,680 --> 01:19:55,440
and, uh, uh, make 'em scream,
hit 'em in the ass. 

1278
01:19:55,520 --> 01:19:58,760
What do you think, Henry?
-Well, as you know, 

1279
01:19:58,840 --> 01:20:02,240
most of my staff have weighed in
against this incursion. 

1280
01:20:02,320 --> 01:20:07,120
They believe it will fail to achieve
anything fundamental militarily

1281
01:20:07,200 --> 01:20:11,120
and will result in crushing criticism
domestically. 

1282
01:20:11,200 --> 01:20:13,280
I didn't ask what your staff thinks.
What do you think, Henry?

1283
01:20:13,360 --> 01:20:16,760
What I think is,
they're cowards. 

1284
01:20:16,840 --> 01:20:21,600
Their opposition represents the
cowardice of the eastern establishment. 

1285
01:20:21,640 --> 01:20:24,560
They don't realize,
as you do, sir, 

1286
01:20:24,640 --> 01:20:27,120
that the Communists
only respect strength, 

1287
01:20:27,200 --> 01:20:29,560
and they will only negotiate
in good faith

1288
01:20:29,640 --> 01:20:32,920
if they fear the mad man, Nixon.
-Exactly!

1289
01:20:33,000 --> 01:20:35,840
Unpredictability is our best asset. 

1290
01:20:35,880 --> 01:20:38,320
We gotta take the war to 'em, hit'em
where it hurts, right in the nuts. 

1291
01:20:38,400 --> 01:20:40,640
More assassinations.
Right, Al?

1292
01:20:40,680 --> 01:20:43,680
That's what they're doing,
Mr. President. 

1293
01:20:43,760 --> 01:20:46,960
See, your people in the State
Department, Bill, they don't understand. 

1294
01:20:47,040 --> 01:20:48,960
You gotta--
-Mr. President. 

1295
01:20:49,000 --> 01:20:51,400
You gotta electrify people with bold
moves. I mean, bold moves make history. 

1296
01:20:51,440 --> 01:20:54,560
Like, uh, Teddy Roosevelt,
T. R. , 

1297
01:20:54,600 --> 01:20:56,840
rushing up San Juan Hill. 

1298
01:20:56,880 --> 01:20:59,040
Small event, but dramatic.
People took notice. 

1299
01:20:59,080 --> 01:21:01,400
Yes, well, they'll take notice,
all right. 

1300
01:21:01,480 --> 01:21:03,720
If we sneak out of this war, 

1301
01:21:03,760 --> 01:21:06,160
another will start
a mile down the road. 

1302
01:21:06,240 --> 01:21:09,960
We bite the bullet here
in Cambodia. There. 

1303
01:21:10,000 --> 01:21:13,120
We bomb the hell
out of these people. 

1304
01:21:17,440 --> 01:21:19,800
Tonight American
and South Vietnamese units

1305
01:21:19,880 --> 01:21:24,040
will attack the headquarters of the
entire Communist military operation

1306
01:21:24,080 --> 01:21:25,560
in South Vietnam. 

1307
01:21:25,640 --> 01:21:29,440
This is not an invasion
of Cambodia. 

1308
01:21:29,480 --> 01:21:34,360
We take this action not for the purpose
of expanding the war into Cambodia, 

1309
01:21:34,440 --> 01:21:37,040
but for the purpose
of ending the war in Vietnam. 

1310
01:21:40,280 --> 01:21:43,600
All across the nation, 

1311
01:21:43,680 --> 01:21:46,400
major student protests against
the U. S. invasion of Cambodia

1312
01:21:46,440 --> 01:21:48,560
rocked college campuses. 

1313
01:21:48,640 --> 01:21:52,160
At Jackson State, two Negro students
were killed and ten were wounded. 

1314
01:21:52,200 --> 01:21:55,520
Unanimously united behind--
-In the streets of New York City, 

1315
01:21:55,600 --> 01:21:58,080
student protesters were attacked
by construction workers

1316
01:21:58,120 --> 01:22:00,040
supporting President Nixon's policies. 

1317
01:22:02,440 --> 01:22:05,680
In Washington, protesters have
barricaded the White House

1318
01:22:05,760 --> 01:22:08,680
and are camping out
at the Lincoln Memorial. 

1319
01:22:10,920 --> 01:22:13,640
We don't want your fucking war!

1320
01:22:18,240 --> 01:22:21,600
See, when I think of those kids
out there in Vietnam, doing their duty, 

1321
01:22:21,680 --> 01:22:23,800
uh, I bet they were scared. 

1322
01:22:23,880 --> 01:22:26,120
I-I was
when I was there. 

1323
01:22:26,160 --> 01:22:28,400
But when it comes down to it, you
really have to look up to these men

1324
01:22:28,480 --> 01:22:30,560
because they're
the greatest. 

1325
01:22:33,840 --> 01:22:36,400
No more war! No more war!

1326
01:22:36,480 --> 01:22:39,320
I mean, you see these bums,
you know, blowing up the campuses, 

1327
01:22:39,400 --> 01:22:41,600
burning books
and so forth. 

1328
01:22:41,680 --> 01:22:44,360
And they call themselves,
uh, flower children. 

1329
01:22:44,440 --> 01:22:46,280
I call them spoiled rotten. 

1330
01:22:46,360 --> 01:22:48,400
And I tell you what
would cure them. 

1331
01:22:48,480 --> 01:22:51,880
A good, old-fashioned trip
to my Ohio father's woodshed. 

1332
01:22:51,960 --> 01:22:53,840
Right, Julie?
-Right, Dad. 

1333
01:22:53,920 --> 01:22:57,400
That's what these bums need. Well, Kurt,
thanks and congratulations. 

1334
01:22:57,480 --> 01:23:01,400
Thank you, sir.
-Yeah. Okay. Thanks, everybody. Bye. 

1335
01:23:21,840 --> 01:23:25,520
Less than 24 hours
after president Nixon called them bums, 

1336
01:23:25,600 --> 01:23:29,520
four students were shot dead
at Kent State University in Ohio. 

1337
01:23:29,600 --> 01:23:32,120
Enraged student groups
across the country

1338
01:23:32,200 --> 01:23:34,800
are calling for a general strike tomorrow to shut down the

entire university system until the Vietnam War is ended. 

1339
01:23:34,880 --> 01:23:38,880
I tell you, the soldiers were provoked.
Now, stop this pussyfooting around. 

1340
01:23:38,960 --> 01:23:42,280
I mean, dead kids. How the hell did we
give the Democrats a weapon like this?

1341
01:23:42,360 --> 01:23:45,880
Well, one way or the other,
Kent State is not good. 

1342
01:23:45,960 --> 01:23:47,800
We have to get out
in front of this thing. 

1343
01:23:47,880 --> 01:23:51,360
Follow the money. Follow the money.
-Sir?

1344
01:23:51,400 --> 01:23:53,920
These kids are being manipulated
by the Communists, 

1345
01:23:53,960 --> 01:23:55,880
like Chambers and Hiss. 

1346
01:23:55,960 --> 01:24:00,040
What's the matter with you?
-This isn't'48. They'll never buy it. 

1347
01:24:00,080 --> 01:24:03,400
How do you know that, John?
What's Hoover found, for God's sake?

1348
01:24:03,480 --> 01:24:06,160
Well, he called the other day, sir.
He asked for President Harding. 

1349
01:24:08,640 --> 01:24:11,760
We can have a national prayer day.
-Never complain, never explain. 

1350
01:24:11,840 --> 01:24:15,480
Come on, these are not
fraternity pranks, John. 

1351
01:24:15,560 --> 01:24:17,800
No, this is anarchy.
It's a revolution. 

1352
01:24:17,880 --> 01:24:20,200
I wouldn't go that far, sir.
-Why not?

1353
01:24:21,640 --> 01:24:24,000
Is it worth it, sir?
I mean--

1354
01:24:24,040 --> 01:24:28,440
Is the war worth a one-term presidency?
Because that's what we're looking at. 

1355
01:24:28,520 --> 01:24:30,600
I will not go down as the first
American president to lose a war. 

1356
01:24:30,680 --> 01:24:32,880
Going to Cambodia,
bombing Hanoi, bombing Laos, 

1357
01:24:32,960 --> 01:24:37,280
buys us time so we can get out and give
the South Vietnamese a fighting chance. 

1358
01:24:37,360 --> 01:24:41,080
Exactly, sir.
-If we keep our heads, we'll win. 

1359
01:24:41,160 --> 01:24:43,520
What, win Vietnam, sir?
-No, no. 

1360
01:24:43,600 --> 01:24:48,600
No, but we can drive a stake through
the heart of the Communist alliance. 

1361
01:24:48,680 --> 01:24:51,680
Henry's getting strong signals
from the Chinese. 

1362
01:24:51,760 --> 01:24:54,280
They fear the Vietnamese
more than the Russians

1363
01:24:54,360 --> 01:24:57,200
and they're worried
about a united Vietnam. 

1364
01:24:57,240 --> 01:25:00,040
Now, if we stick it out,
we'll end up negotiating separately

1365
01:25:00,120 --> 01:25:02,760
with both the Chinese
and the Soviets. 

1366
01:25:02,800 --> 01:25:05,840
And we'll get better deals
than we ever dreamed of from both. 

1367
01:25:05,920 --> 01:25:09,640
That is triangular diplomacy,
gentlemen. 

1368
01:25:09,720 --> 01:25:11,520
Exactly,
Mr. President. 

1369
01:25:11,560 --> 01:25:14,160
That's what geopolitics
is about. 

1370
01:25:14,240 --> 01:25:17,600
The linking of the whole world
for self-interest. 

1371
01:25:17,680 --> 01:25:21,960
Ron, how I can explain that on TV
to a bunch of simpleminded reporters

1372
01:25:22,000 --> 01:25:23,880
and, uh, weeping mothers. 

1373
01:25:23,960 --> 01:25:26,440
Yeah, but what am I telling
the press about Kent State?

1374
01:25:26,480 --> 01:25:29,400
Ah, tell 'em what the hell you like.
They don't understand anyway. 

1375
01:25:29,480 --> 01:25:32,280
Excuse me, sir. 

1376
01:25:32,360 --> 01:25:35,040
Are you saying you're going
to recognize Red China?

1377
01:25:35,120 --> 01:25:38,120
That would cost us
our strongest support. 

1378
01:25:38,200 --> 01:25:41,000
No, I can do this because
I spent my whole career

1379
01:25:41,040 --> 01:25:43,280
building anti-Communist
credentials. 

1380
01:25:43,360 --> 01:25:47,480
If Kennedy or Johnson tried it, they'd
have crucified them, and rightfully so. 

1381
01:25:47,560 --> 01:25:51,000
Damned risky, Mr. President.
Why don't we wait until the second term?

1382
01:25:51,080 --> 01:25:53,880
This will get us a second term, John.
-This will get me a second term. 

1383
01:25:53,960 --> 01:25:57,720
Damn it, without risk,
there's no heroism, there's no history. 

1384
01:25:57,800 --> 01:26:00,600
Nixon was born to do this.
Give history a nudge. 

1385
01:26:00,680 --> 01:26:02,120
Come on!
-Hear, hear. 

1386
01:26:02,200 --> 01:26:06,240
I mean, if Cambodia doesn't work
we'll bomb Hanoi if we have to. 

1387
01:26:06,280 --> 01:26:09,720
That's right. And if necessary,
I'll drop the big one. 

1388
01:26:13,240 --> 01:26:15,840
We have to entertain
the possibility. 

1389
01:26:21,000 --> 01:26:23,720
Goddamn it!
Who cooked this damn steak?

1390
01:26:23,800 --> 01:26:25,920
Manolo, there's blood all over my plate.
Take it away. 

1391
01:26:25,960 --> 01:26:27,840
I'm sorry, sir. 

1392
01:26:40,440 --> 01:26:42,760
Are you all right?

1393
01:26:42,840 --> 01:26:45,760
Yeah. 

1394
01:26:45,840 --> 01:26:49,640
My brother, Harold, was the same age
as those kids, John. 

1395
01:26:49,680 --> 01:26:53,960
Tuberculosis got him.
-Come on, it wasn't your fault. 

1396
01:26:54,040 --> 01:26:57,760
The soldiers were kids too.
They just panicked. 

1397
01:26:57,800 --> 01:27:00,200
Yeah. 

1398
01:27:00,240 --> 01:27:03,120
They were throwing rocks,
John, just rocks. 

1399
01:27:06,440 --> 01:27:08,320
They don't think I feel, 

1400
01:27:08,360 --> 01:27:11,880
but I feel too much
sometimes. 

1401
01:27:12,680 --> 01:27:16,760
I just can't let our whole policy
be dominated by our sentimentality. 

1402
01:27:16,840 --> 01:27:20,280
You're doing the right thing.
Don't let 'em shake you. 

1403
01:27:20,360 --> 01:27:22,560
No. 

1404
01:27:22,600 --> 01:27:25,880
You know, it broke my heart
when Harold died. 

1405
01:27:25,920 --> 01:27:30,680
That was a long time ago.
-Yeah. 

1406
01:27:30,760 --> 01:27:34,760
I think that's when it starts--
when you're a kid. 

1407
01:27:34,840 --> 01:27:38,160
