So, that's where the money came from.
That's all I own. 

2550
02:39:27,800 --> 02:39:30,680
That's what we have,
and that's what we owe. 

2551
02:39:30,720 --> 02:39:33,880
Because people have got to know
whether or not their... 

2552
02:39:33,920 --> 02:39:35,800
... president is a crook. 

2553
02:39:35,840 --> 02:39:38,160
Well, I am not a crook. 

2554
02:39:38,240 --> 02:39:41,040
I've earned everything I have... 

2555
02:39:41,120 --> 02:39:44,240
She does have a respectable
Republican cloth coat. 

2556
02:39:44,320 --> 02:39:47,480
And I always tell her, uh,
she'd look good in anything. 

2557
02:39:47,560 --> 02:39:50,400
There has never been
any feathering of nests. 

2558
02:39:50,480 --> 02:39:52,800
Not in this
administration. 

2559
02:39:52,880 --> 02:39:55,120
Now, let me just say this... 

2560
02:39:55,160 --> 02:39:58,480
And I want to say this
to the television audience. 

2561
02:39:58,520 --> 02:40:01,600
The Supreme Court ruled today eight to
nothing that President Nixon's claims... 

2562
02:40:01,680 --> 02:40:04,680
... of executive privilege
cannot be used in criminal cases... 

2563
02:40:04,760 --> 02:40:07,880
... and must turn over subpoenaed tapes.
The House Judiciary Committee... 

2564
02:40:07,960 --> 02:40:09,800
... has voted 27 to 11

2565
02:40:09,880 --> 02:40:12,200
... to recommend impeachment
to the full House. 

2566
02:40:12,240 --> 02:40:15,080
The deliberations now go
to the House floor. 

2567
02:40:15,120 --> 02:40:18,440
In its report, the committee offers
evidence Nixon obstructed justice... 

2568
02:40:18,520 --> 02:40:20,400
... on at least 36 occasions... 

2569
02:40:20,480 --> 02:40:22,680
... that he encouraged his aides
to commit perjury... 

2570
02:40:22,760 --> 02:40:25,600
... and that Nixon abused
the powers of his office. 

2571
02:40:25,640 --> 02:40:28,000
In a separate report,
the Senate Select committee... 

2572
02:40:28,080 --> 02:40:29,920
... details the misuse
of the I. R. S. 

2573
02:40:30,000 --> 02:40:33,840
... the F. B. I. , the C. I. A.
and the justice department. 

2574
02:40:33,920 --> 02:40:36,600
It denounces the plumbers
and it raises the question... 

2575
02:40:36,640 --> 02:40:40,800
... of whether the United States
had a valid election in 1972. 

2576
02:40:53,240 --> 02:40:55,320
Come in. 

2577
02:41:05,960 --> 02:41:09,720
Victory at Sea, Al.
Henry. 

2578
02:41:09,800 --> 02:41:12,120
The Pacific Theatre. 

2579
02:41:12,200 --> 02:41:16,440
Christ, you can almost hear
the waves breaking over the decks. 

2580
02:41:21,760 --> 02:41:24,600
I'm afraid we have another problem,
Mr. President. 

2581
02:41:24,680 --> 02:41:26,520
Excuse me, gentlemen. 

2582
02:41:30,880 --> 02:41:33,040
June 23rd, '72, sir. 

2583
02:41:36,320 --> 02:41:40,880
Your instructions to Haldeman
regarding the C. I. A. and the F. B. I. 

2584
02:41:40,960 --> 02:41:43,520
So?

2585
02:41:43,600 --> 02:41:45,920
Your lawyers
feel that... 

2586
02:41:46,000 --> 02:41:48,160
... it's
the smoking gun. 

2587
02:41:48,240 --> 02:41:51,320
That's totally out of context.
I was protecting the national security. 

2588
02:41:51,440 --> 02:41:53,240
Sir, the deadline
is today. 

2589
02:41:56,360 --> 02:41:58,800
Can we get around this,
Al?

2590
02:41:59,840 --> 02:42:01,840
It's the Supreme Court,
sir. 

2591
02:42:01,920 --> 02:42:04,440
You don't get around it. 

2592
02:42:07,680 --> 02:42:10,160
If, uh... 

2593
02:42:10,240 --> 02:42:14,480
If you resign, you can keep your tapes
as a private citizen. 

2594
02:42:14,560 --> 02:42:17,000
You could fight them
For years. 

2595
02:42:19,320 --> 02:42:21,560
What if I stay?

2596
02:42:23,800 --> 02:42:25,680
You have the army. 

2597
02:42:26,680 --> 02:42:28,480
The army?

2598
02:42:29,920 --> 02:42:31,760
Lincoln used it. 

2599
02:42:37,440 --> 02:42:39,800
We'll have civil war. 

2600
02:42:39,840 --> 02:42:42,360
How do you see this?

2601
02:42:45,280 --> 02:42:47,200
Oh, God. 

2602
02:42:47,280 --> 02:42:49,840
We can't survive this,
sir. 

2603
02:42:52,680 --> 02:42:54,520
They also... 

2604
02:42:54,600 --> 02:42:57,560
... have you instructing Dean
to make the pay off to Hunt. 

2605
02:42:57,600 --> 02:43:01,400
There's nothing in that statement
the president can't explain. 

2606
02:43:01,480 --> 02:43:06,640
Sir, you talked about opening up
the whole Bay of Pigs thing again. 

2607
02:43:06,720 --> 02:43:09,920
That's right.
On the June 20 tape. 

2608
02:43:10,000 --> 02:43:12,320
The one with
the 18-minute gap. 

2609
02:43:12,360 --> 02:43:13,560
I don't know anything
about that. 

2610
02:43:13,640 --> 02:43:16,440
You mentioned the Bay of Pigs
several times. 

2611
02:43:16,520 --> 02:43:20,320
Sooner or later, they're going to
want to know what that means. 

2612
02:43:20,400 --> 02:43:23,200
They're going to want to
know what's on that gap. 

2613
02:43:23,280 --> 02:43:26,680
It's gone. No one will ever
find out what's on it. 

2614
02:43:28,480 --> 02:43:31,320
They might... 

2615
02:43:31,360 --> 02:43:33,280
... if there was
another recording. 

2616
02:43:34,800 --> 02:43:37,320
We both know
it's possible. 

2617
02:43:40,800 --> 02:43:43,160
I know for a fact... 

2618
02:43:43,240 --> 02:43:45,840
... that it's possible. 

2619
02:43:48,400 --> 02:43:50,280
I've spoken to Ford. 

2620
02:43:50,320 --> 02:43:52,520
There's
a very strong chance... 

2621
02:43:52,560 --> 02:43:54,440
... that he'll pardon you. 

2622
02:43:54,480 --> 02:43:57,800
I don't need a goddamned deal,
for God's sake. I... 

2623
02:43:57,880 --> 02:44:02,000
This is something that
you will have to do, Mr. President. 

2624
02:44:05,080 --> 02:44:07,440
I thought
you'd rather do it... 

2625
02:44:07,480 --> 02:44:09,360
... now. 

2626
02:44:13,320 --> 02:44:15,160
I'll wait outside. 

2627
02:44:20,200 --> 02:44:22,840
Sir. 

2628
02:44:22,920 --> 02:44:26,680
May I say, sir,
that if you stay now... 

2629
02:44:26,760 --> 02:44:30,840
... it will paralyze the nation
and its foreign policy. 

2630
02:44:33,800 --> 02:44:37,320
You always had a great
sense of timing, Henry. 

2631
02:44:37,400 --> 02:44:39,640
When to give... 

2632
02:44:39,720 --> 02:44:41,560
... and when to take. 

2633
02:44:43,880 --> 02:44:47,800
How do you think Mao
and Brezhnev will react?

2634
02:44:47,880 --> 02:44:50,880
Do you think they'll
remember us, Henry... 

2635
02:44:50,960 --> 02:44:53,520
... after all the great things
you and I did together... 

2636
02:44:53,560 --> 02:44:56,480
... as some kind of... 

2637
02:44:56,560 --> 02:44:58,400
... of crooks?

2638
02:44:58,480 --> 02:45:00,560
They will understand. 

2639
02:45:00,640 --> 02:45:05,520
To be undone by a third-rate burglary
is a fate of biblical proportions. 

2640
02:45:08,160 --> 02:45:11,760
History will treat you far more kindly
than your contemporaries. 

2641
02:45:11,800 --> 02:45:16,040
Yeah. Depends who writes
the history books. 

2642
02:45:17,400 --> 02:45:20,560
I'm not a quitter,
never have been. 

2643
02:45:20,640 --> 02:45:23,640
But I'm not stupid either. 

2644
02:45:23,680 --> 02:45:27,120
A trial would kill me.
That's what they want. 

2645
02:45:27,200 --> 02:45:29,600
They won't get it. 

2646
02:45:29,680 --> 02:45:31,960
Fuck 'em. 

2647
02:45:52,080 --> 02:45:56,200
If they harass you, I too will resign,
and I will tell the world why. 

2648
02:45:56,280 --> 02:46:00,680
Don't be stupid.
The world needs you, Henry. 

2649
02:46:00,760 --> 02:46:02,560
You always saw
the big picture. 

2650
02:46:07,040 --> 02:46:09,360
You were my equal
in many ways. 

2651
02:46:18,960 --> 02:46:21,800
You're the only friend
I got, Henry. 

2652
02:46:24,080 --> 02:46:25,960
Do you ever pray?

2653
02:46:27,520 --> 02:46:32,840
You know, believe
in a supreme being?

2654
02:46:34,080 --> 02:46:36,440
Uh, not really. 

2655
02:46:36,520 --> 02:46:38,520
You mean on my knees?

2656
02:46:42,120 --> 02:46:44,600
My mother used to pray
a lot. 

2657
02:46:46,160 --> 02:46:50,320
It's been a long time
since I really prayed. 

2658
02:46:55,880 --> 02:46:57,760
Let's pray, Henry. 

2659
02:46:59,000 --> 02:47:01,440
Let's pray a little. 

2660
02:47:01,520 --> 02:47:04,280
Just you and me. 

2661
02:47:11,000 --> 02:47:13,480
I hope this doesn't
embarrass you, Henry. 

2662
02:47:13,560 --> 02:47:16,240
No. Not at all, no. 

2663
02:47:16,280 --> 02:47:18,560
This is not going to leak, is it?

2664
02:47:22,600 --> 02:47:25,840
Don't be too proud,
Henry. 

2665
02:47:25,880 --> 02:47:29,680
Never be too proud
to go on your knees before God. 

2666
02:47:41,840 --> 02:47:44,160
God. 

2667
02:47:50,240 --> 02:47:52,320
How can a... 

2668
02:47:52,400 --> 02:47:54,800
How can a country
come apart like this?

2669
02:47:55,920 --> 02:47:58,240
What have I done wrong?

2670
02:48:00,040 --> 02:48:02,440
I opened China. 

2671
02:48:02,480 --> 02:48:05,080
I made peace
with Russia. 

2672
02:48:05,160 --> 02:48:07,000
I ended the war. 

2673
02:48:09,440 --> 02:48:11,760
I did what I thought
was right. 

2674
02:48:15,200 --> 02:48:18,160
Uh... 

2675
02:48:18,240 --> 02:48:20,680
God, why do they
hate me so?

2676
02:48:20,760 --> 02:48:24,800
It's unbelievable.
It... It's insane. 

2677
02:48:24,880 --> 02:48:29,520
Oh, M-Mom, I'm sorry.
God, please forgive me, God. 

2678
02:48:29,560 --> 02:48:32,720
I didn't mean it.
I didn't know what to do. 

2679
02:48:32,760 --> 02:48:36,080
I don't know why
this is happening to me. 

2680
02:48:36,160 --> 02:48:38,480
I can't believe... 

2681
02:48:44,240 --> 02:48:46,480
Al. 

2682
02:49:00,920 --> 02:49:03,600
They smelled the blood
on me this time, Al. 

2683
02:49:03,680 --> 02:49:06,480
I got soft, you know?

2684
02:49:06,520 --> 02:49:10,160
A rusty, metallic smell. 

2685
02:49:10,200 --> 02:49:12,080
I know it well, sir. 

2686
02:49:12,120 --> 02:49:14,600
It came over from Vietnam,
you know?

2687
02:49:14,680 --> 02:49:17,920
Sir?
That smell. 

2688
02:49:18,000 --> 02:49:21,040
I mean, everyone
suffered so much. 

2689
02:49:21,120 --> 02:49:24,240
Their boys killed. 

2690
02:49:24,320 --> 02:49:27,760
Uh, they need to
sacrifice something. 

2691
02:49:27,840 --> 02:49:30,720
You know, appease
the gods of war. 

2692
02:49:30,800 --> 02:49:33,640
Mars, Jupiter. 

2693
02:49:37,200 --> 02:49:39,120
I am that blood,
General. 

2694
02:49:42,120 --> 02:49:43,960
I am that sacrifice. 

2695
02:49:45,520 --> 02:49:47,400
In the highest place
of all. 

2696
02:49:51,440 --> 02:49:55,800
Yeah. All leaders must
finally be sacrificed. 

2697
02:49:55,880 --> 02:49:59,680
Things won't be the same
after this. 

2698
02:49:59,760 --> 02:50:01,800
No, I played
by the rules. 

2699
02:50:01,840 --> 02:50:05,360
Rules changed right
in the middle of the game. 

2700
02:50:05,440 --> 02:50:08,720
There's no respect
for American institutions anymore. 

2701
02:50:08,760 --> 02:50:13,480
No, people are cynical. 

2702
02:50:13,520 --> 02:50:16,520
The press... ah, the press
is out of control. 

2703
02:50:18,280 --> 02:50:21,600
People spit on soldiers. 

2704
02:50:21,680 --> 02:50:24,240
Government secrets mean nothing. 

2705
02:50:25,520 --> 02:50:27,880
I pity the next guy
who sits here. 

2706
02:50:31,080 --> 02:50:32,920
Good night,
gentlemen. 

2707
02:50:38,720 --> 02:50:40,560
Mr. President. 

2708
02:51:16,440 --> 02:51:18,920
When they look at you... 

2709
02:51:19,000 --> 02:51:21,320
... they see
what they want to be. 

2710
02:51:23,720 --> 02:51:26,720
When they look at me... 

2711
02:51:26,800 --> 02:51:29,120
... they see what they are. 

2712
02:51:33,680 --> 02:51:36,840
Dick, please don't. 

2713
02:51:42,840 --> 02:51:45,200
I can't. 

2714
02:51:45,240 --> 02:51:48,120
I don't have
the strength anymore. 

2715
02:51:49,360 --> 02:51:51,680
It'll be over soon. 

2716
02:51:51,760 --> 02:51:55,360
No, it's going to start now. 

2717
02:51:55,440 --> 02:51:58,120
Oh, Buddy. 

2718
02:51:58,160 --> 02:52:00,160
If I could just sleep. 

2719
02:52:00,360 --> 02:52:02,200
If I could just sleep. 

2720
02:52:02,280 --> 02:52:04,880
There'll be time for that.
Yeah. 

2721
02:52:09,800 --> 02:52:11,920
You know, once... 

2722
02:52:11,960 --> 02:52:14,520
... when I was sick as a boy... 

2723
02:52:14,600 --> 02:52:17,840
... my mother gave me
this stuff... 

2724
02:52:17,880 --> 02:52:20,560
... and she made me
swallow it. 

2725
02:52:20,600 --> 02:52:22,960
It made me throw up
all over her. 

2726
02:52:26,120 --> 02:52:29,120
I wish I could
do that now. 

2727
02:52:34,600 --> 02:52:37,720
I'm so afraid. 

2728
02:52:37,800 --> 02:52:40,120
There's darkness out there. 

2729
02:52:42,480 --> 02:52:45,960
I could always see
where I was going. 

2730
02:52:46,040 --> 02:52:47,880
But it's dark out there. 

2731
02:52:49,280 --> 02:52:53,240
God, I've always been
afraid of the dark. 

2732
02:52:55,440 --> 02:52:57,760
Buddy. 

2733
02:53:23,440 --> 02:53:25,960
There are many fine careers. 

2734
02:53:26,000 --> 02:53:28,680
This country needs
good farmers... 

2735
02:53:28,760 --> 02:53:33,720
... good businessmen,
good plumbers... 

2736
02:53:33,800 --> 02:53:35,640
... good carpenters. 

2737
02:53:36,920 --> 02:53:38,760
I remember my old man. 

2738
02:53:40,120 --> 02:53:43,480
I think that they would have
called him sort of a... 

2739
02:53:43,560 --> 02:53:46,600
... sort of a little man,
a common man. 

2740
02:53:46,680 --> 02:53:50,280
Well, he didn't consider
himself that way. 

2741
02:53:51,320 --> 02:53:54,160
You know what he was?

2742
02:53:54,240 --> 02:53:56,680
He was a streetcar motorman first. 

2743
02:53:56,760 --> 02:54:00,240
Then he was a farmer. 

2744
02:54:00,320 --> 02:54:02,160
Then he had a lemon ranch. 

2745
02:54:02,240 --> 02:54:05,680
It was the poorest lemon ranch
in California, I can assure you. 

2746
02:54:05,760 --> 02:54:08,000
He sold it before
they found oil on it. 

2747
02:54:11,600 --> 02:54:14,360
Then he was a grocer. 

2748
02:54:14,440 --> 02:54:16,840
But he was a great man... 

2749
02:54:16,880 --> 02:54:19,360
... because he did his job. 

2750
02:54:19,440 --> 02:54:22,240
And every job counts
up to the hilt... 

2751
02:54:22,320 --> 02:54:25,720
... regardless of what happens. 

2752
02:54:25,800 --> 02:54:30,400
Nobody will ever write a book,
probably, about my mother. 

2753
02:54:30,440 --> 02:54:33,280
Well, I guess
all of you would... 

2754
02:54:33,360 --> 02:54:36,040
... say this
about your mother. 

2755
02:54:37,680 --> 02:54:40,960
My mother was a saint. 

2756
02:54:41,040 --> 02:54:42,880
And I think of her... 

2757
02:54:42,960 --> 02:54:46,520
... two boys dying
of tuberculosis... 

2758
02:54:46,600 --> 02:54:49,240
... and seeing each of them die. 

2759
02:54:49,320 --> 02:54:51,160
And when they died... 

2760
02:54:55,320 --> 02:54:59,880
Yes, she will have no books
written about her. 

2761
02:55:01,720 --> 02:55:04,520
But she was a saint. 

2762
02:55:05,560 --> 02:55:09,000
Now, however,
we look to the future. 

2763
02:55:10,440 --> 02:55:14,120
I remember something, uh,
Theodore Roosevelt wrote... 

2764
02:55:14,200 --> 02:55:16,320
... when his first wife died... 

2765
02:55:16,400 --> 02:55:18,400
... in his twenties. 

2766
02:55:18,440 --> 02:55:21,520
He thought the light
had gone from his life forever. 

2767
02:55:21,600 --> 02:55:25,680
But he went on, and he
not only became president... 

2768
02:55:25,760 --> 02:55:28,240
... but as an ex-president,
he served his country... 

2769
02:55:28,320 --> 02:55:32,160
... always in the arena,
tempestuous, strong... 

2770
02:55:32,240 --> 02:55:34,880
... sometimes right,
sometimes wrong. 

2771
02:55:34,920 --> 02:55:37,120
But he was a man. 

2772
02:55:37,200 --> 02:55:39,760
And as I leave... 

2773
02:55:39,840 --> 02:55:43,560
... that's an example I think
all of us should remember. 

2774
02:55:43,640 --> 02:55:46,280
See, we think sometimes
when, uh... 

2775
02:55:46,320 --> 02:55:49,000
... things happen
that don't go the right way;

2776
02:55:49,040 --> 02:55:52,760
... we think that when someone
dear to us dies... 

2777
02:55:52,840 --> 02:55:55,200
... uh, when we lose
an election... 

2778
02:55:55,280 --> 02:55:57,440
... or when we suffer defeat... 

2779
02:55:57,520 --> 02:55:59,360
... that all is ended. 

2780
02:55:59,440 --> 02:56:01,280
Not true. 

2781
02:56:01,360 --> 02:56:03,920
It's only a beginning,
always... 

2782
02:56:04,000 --> 02:56:07,720
... because the greatness comes,
not when things go always good for you... 

2783
02:56:07,800 --> 02:56:09,800
... but the greatness comes... 

2784
02:56:09,840 --> 02:56:11,760
... when you're really tested... 

2785
02:56:11,840 --> 02:56:15,280
... when you take some knocks,
some disappointments... 

2786
02:56:15,360 --> 02:56:17,480
... when sadness comes. 

2787
02:56:17,560 --> 02:56:21,360
Because only if you've been
in the deepest valley... 

2788
02:56:21,440 --> 02:56:25,200
... can you ever know
how magnificent it is... 

2789
02:56:26,880 --> 02:56:29,280
... to be on the highest mountain. 

2790
02:56:32,960 --> 02:56:35,760
So I say to you on this occasion... 

2791
02:56:35,840 --> 02:56:38,720
... we leave, proud of the people
who have stood by us... 

2792
02:56:38,800 --> 02:56:43,240
... and worked for us and served
this government and this country. 

